  "Broker Comment" : "2/25/98 - APPEALED TO THE NAC.  4/9/99 - NAC DECISION RENDERED 3/31/99, WHEREIN THE FINDINGS MADE ARE AFFIRMED AND THE SANCTIONS IMPOSED AGAINST GALLAGHER ARE MODIFIED; THEREFORE, HE IS CENSURED AND FINED $5,000, AND REQUIRED TO REQUALIFY AS A GENERAL SECURITIES PRINCIPAL WITHIN 60 DAYS FO THE DATE OF THE DECISION.  GALLAGHER MUST ALSO DEMONSTRATE TO THE NASD WITHIN THAT 60 DAY PERIOD THAT HIS FIRM, W.J. GALLAGHER & CO. HAD PUT INTO PLACE AN EFFECTIVE SYSTEM TO SUPERVISE ACTIVITIES AT THE FIRM'S OSJ.  5/6/99 - APPEAL TO SEC.  12/23/1999 - THE SEC SUSTAINED THE NASD'S DISCIPLINARY ACTION AGAINST GLIKSMAN AND GALLAGHER.  THE SEC REJECTED GALLAGHER'S ARGUMENT THAT HE HAD DELEGATED SUPERVISION OVER GLIKSMAN TO ANOTHER PERSON IN GLIKSMAN'S BRANCH OFFICE.  THE SEC FOUND THAT PERSON WAS NOT QUALIFIED AS A GENERAL SECURITIES PRINCIPAL AND THUS COUND NOT SUPERVISE GLIKSMAN.  THE SEC FOUND THAT GALLAGHER FAILED TO IMPLEMENT PROCEDURES TO DETECT EXCESSIVE TRADING AND FAILED TO OBTAIN COPIES OF CRITICAL ACCOUNT DOCUMENTS (RELS. 34-42255; FILE NO. 3-9891)  2/14/00 - SEC ORDERED A STAY OF ITS 12/21/99 DECISION IN THIS MATTER PENDING THE POSSIBLE FILING OF AN APPEAL WITH THE U.S. COURT OF APPEALS.  THE SANCTIONS IMPOSED BY THE NASD ARE STAYED FOR 60 DAYS FROM THE 12/21/99 DECISION.  APPEALED TO THE U.S. COURT OF APPEALS ON 2/2/00."
